<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1253.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department learns from the American group that the consortium is not
                            threatened by the proposed advance to be made independently by the
                            British and German bankers, but that this advance if made would be open
                            to participation by the other groups as required by the quadruple and
                            sextuple inter-group agreements.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>